    <sharedRules>
        <rule name="Synapse (Aura)" id="fe2a-828e-703a-4c5e" hidden="false">
            <description>Units within 12" of a model with this ability resolve Leadership based tests with no modification. If it fails the test the unit loses wounds equal to the difference between its moral value and the result rolled. No saving throws may be applied to prevent this wound loss. If a unit with Battleshock Tokens enters Synapse range or starts the Reserve Phase in it, it immediately loses its tokens. Models with this ability gain a Moral Value of 12 and cannot use Rapid Adaptation Tokens.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Shadow in the Warp" id="24cc-9e7f-ab93-457f" hidden="false">
            <description>Replace the "Perils of the Warp" chart with the Shadow in the Warp chart as follows</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="In the Eye of the Swarm" id="f289-0bbb-a13f-4942" hidden="false">
            <description>The Psyker and all units with one model in a 12" radius suffer a -1 penality to their moral value until the Psyker is activated again.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Insatiable Hunger" id="8355-6f85-96a7-4b2a" hidden="false">
            <description>The Psyker immediately resolves all its close combat attacks against one model within 3" if there is no model within 3" it targets itself.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Psyonic Cannibalism" id="6c0a-0357-99db-4624" hidden="false">
            <description>One friendly model within 12" loses one wound and the Psyker regenerates one if it is wounded. If there is no friendly model within 12" of the Psyker loses one wound. No saving throws are allowed against either of these wound loses.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Paranioa" id="d73a-42ef-dd63-4f38" hidden="false">
            <description>The Psyker suffers a -1 malus to its moral value until the game ends. This result is cumulative with additional Paranioa results.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="They are here! " id="712b-def4-bed2-4cc6" hidden="false">
            <description>The Psyker and all units with a model within 12" do not suffer any penalities when using the "Defensive Fire" reaction. If the Psyker has the Keyword "Synapse" all units with a model within 12" must lay open their unresolved orders instead.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="No Hope" id="9bc2-2184-3d3d-4e65" hidden="false">
            <description>ALL units with ONE Battleshock Token must take an unmodified moral check or gain another token. The Player who lost the initiative starts resolving the outcome of this result.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Rapid Adaptation" id="0261-ccd9-31ce-40a9" hidden="false">
            <description>If a friendly Tyranid unit is destroyed you gain a Rapid Adaptation Token. You can use this token in the Rally Phase of the next turn on any unit that has a model within reach of a model with the abilty Synapse. Models with the ability Synapse may use Rapid Adaptation Tokens on themselves. The unit can choose one of the following boni +1 WS, +1 BS or +1T. It has no effect to have multiple tokens on one unit. The effect lasts until the end of the turn. Unused tokens are lost at the end of the turn.</description>
        </rule>
    </sharedRules>
